    <li><I>Prince v. Massachusetts</I>.
    <li>See Patrick F. Fagan, "Promoting Adoption Reform: Congress Can Give Children Another Chance," Heritage Founation <I>Backgrounder</I> No. 1080, May 6, 1996.
    <li> <I>People v. Greene</i>. cit., and <I>Ingraham v. Wright</I>, 430 U.S. 651 (1977).
    <li> <I>Prince v. Massachusetts</I> and <I>Wisconsin v. Yoder</I>.
    <li> <I>Epperson v. Arkansas</I>, 393 U.S. 97 at 104, 21 L.Ed. 2d 228, 89 S. Ct. 266 (1968).
  <li> <I>Mozert v. Hawkins County Bd. of Ed.</I>, 827 F. 2d. 1058 (1987); Cert. denied, 484 U.S. 1066 (1988).
    <li><I>State of Indiana v. Bailey</I>, 157 Indiana 324 (1901).
   <li> Quoted in Margaret O'Brien Steinfels, <I>Who's Minding the Children?: The History and Politics of Day Care in America</I> (New York, N.Y.: Simon & Schuster, 1973), p. 78.
<p>
<BR><HR WIDTH="30%"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/heritage/hbut.map"><IMG SRC="/heritage/hbut.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></CENTER></body></html>



 

 


