<li>    Mackinac Center for Public Policy, "The Right to Know Payroll Form," April 1996. Workers can determine the amount of Social Security and Medicare taxes they pay, as well as their federal and state income taxes, simply by looking at their pay stubs. Employers, however, usually do not report to workers the cost of government-mandated benefits and taxes paid on behalf of their workers.<p>
