from the voters. This  legislation, however, was overturned in 1995 when the
Supreme Court ruled  in <I>U.S. Term Limits v. Thornton</I> that the states had
no  constitutional right to set the terms of their congressional
representatives.</TD><TD COLSTART="2"><B>Alaska, Arizona, 
